review_text: Ayam Hong is Epic

Travelers, there is another bukber spot which is a really unique place. The location is on Jalan Veteran, Central Jakarta. It is said that the name of this restaurant was inspired by a story from the time of Rafless, the governor of the Dutch East Indies who transformed the Rijswijk area, aka Veterans Street, into an elite area for nobles. So it is called Dapur Babah Elite which serves a Peranakan menu with 3 cultural elements. There are the archipelago, the Netherlands and China Whats more unique is that this restaurant also has vintage Chinese-style vibes ornaments and statues that are hundreds of years old. Wow, you will automatically become a native noble in one day, travelers Markiview, lets review the variety of dishes. I spilled the menu that I tried, lets go review! 1) Ball Shrimp (6/5) The prawns are fresh, wrapped in curly noodles. Crunchy on the outside, sweet shrimp meat. Dipped in sweet and sour sauce. Makes a really good appetizer! 2) Ajam Bekem Rice (6.5/5) Typical food from Jombang, East Java. This is really delicious, at first glance it looks like opor. But when I tried it, it was different. The marinade is top notch. It has ointment that makes it lively when you eat it! Its really a winner for the main course. 3) Njonja Babah Soup (5/5) Those who like cream soup will definitely like this menu. Not too overcooked and creamy. Its delicious to eat when its hot. If you are breaking the fast, order this menu, it is best to serve it 1/2 hour before iftar. 4) Shrimp Wrapped Meat Roll (7/5) Wow, this is it! Really recommend it for the main course. Including my favorite. From the first bite, the meat felt really juicy. There is an authentic sauce that makes the taste of this menu even richer. Must try it!! 5) Mango Tea (6/5) Honestly, just tried this menu variant. Brewing lemongrass tea, has a mango aroma. We can adjust the sweetness from liquid sugar to our individual tastes. [Additional Info] Reservations are mandatory considering this restaurant is always fully booked Minimal parking space Premium cookie hampers available starting from 300k Prayer room & mini garden available (still in reservation stage There is a Mini Tao Bar & Kawisari coffee merchandise. All the menus are over rated because in terms of plating + deliciousness they are really great! Plus the vibes are cozy. During the month of Ramadan, there are always full bookings from corporate and government. So those who book personally tend to run out of seats.
review_translated_text: Travelers, ada lagi nih spot bukber yang tempatnya unik banget. Lokasinya ada di jalan veteran Jakarta pusat. Konon, penamaan resto ini terinspirasi dari cerita pada zaman rafless , gubernur Hindia Belanda yang menyulap kawasan Rijswijk alias jalan veteran menjadi kawasan elite bangsawan. Maka bernama Dapur Babah Elite yang menyajikan menu peranakan dengan 3 unsur budaya. Ada Nusantara, Belanda dan Tiongkok Uniknya lagi, di resto ini juga terdapat ornamen vintage vibes ala Tiongkok dan arca yang sudah berusia ratusan tahun. Wah, auto jadi ningrat pribumi dalam sehari ya travelers Markiview, mari kita review ragam hidangannya. Aku spill ya menu yang aku cobain, lets go review! 1) Udang Bola (6/5) Udangnya fresh, dibalut sama mie keriting. Crunchy diluar, manis daging udangnya. Dicocol pake saus asam manis. Buat appetizer oke banget! 2) Nasi Ajam Bekem (6.5/5) Makanan khas Jombang, Jawa Timur. Enak banget ini sih, sekilas mirip opor dari looks nya. Tapi pas dicobain berbeze cyinn. Bumbu marinasinya juara. Ada urap nya yang bikin rame pas nyantap! Juarak sih buat main course nya. 3) Soup Njonja Babah (5/5) Yang doyan cream soup pasti sukaaaa banget sama menu yang satu ini. Gak terlalu overcook dan Creamy. Enak dimakan pas anget-anget sih. Kalo buka puasa order menu ini baiknya disajikan 1/2 jam sebelum iftar. 4) Daging Gulung Bungkus Udang (7/5) Weh ini sih! Aselik rekomen banget buat main course. Termasuk favorit aku. Dari gigitan awal aja udah berasa banget juicy dagingnya. Ada sauce otentiknya yang bikin citarasa dari menu ini makin rich. Wajibbbb cobain!! 5) Mango Tea (6/5) Jujurly baru cobain varian menu ini. Seduhan teh sereh, ada aroma mangga. Manisnya dari gula cair yang bisa kita sesuaikan selera masing-masing. [Tambahan Info] Wajib reservasi mengingat resto ini selalu full booking Minim lahan parkir Tersedia hampers premium cookies mulai dari 300k Tersedia mushola & mini garden (masih dalam tahap reservasi Ada Mini Tao Bar & merchandise perkopian Kawisari. Semua menunya over rate karena dari segi plating + tasty juarak banget sih! Ditambah vibes nya cozy. Selama bulan Ramadhan selalu full booking dari corporate maupun government. Jadi yang booking secara personal suka kehabisan seat.

Wow, wow, wow This place to eat is really cool!!! Actually, this really feels beyond expectations. Here we order: 5/5 Nasik Crab Curry To be honest, I never imagined eating crab cooked with curry spices. I ordered it because its really unique, Ive never seen it anywhere else. When I tried the first bite       oh my gosh, how come youre just eating this delicious food now. So on the plate it is served as follows: White rice Tofu soy sauce Floss Saute the beans Chilli sauce 2pcs rice crackers I think? 1 crab has been split (2 shells, 2 legs and 1 shell) Behind the shell, it turns out its filled with crab meat that has been fried with eggs, I think the crab and eggs are all cooked deep fried (sorry if its sotoy, hahaha). The smell can be delicious, it really smells like eggs combined with the curry sauce. As for the taste of the curry itself, its not the taste of curry in Nasi Padang, its like its a curry fusion, but its really delicious. Its not medok but the taste is just right. If this is a soft shell crab, Im really happy, unfortunately this is a regular crab, its quite big, so cleaning it is a bit of a hassle (the place is so aesthetic, but you have to clean it with your hands, its difficult, bro) 5/5 Tugu Spice Boentoet Rice When I arrived, it was a bit under estimated. The only problem is: Rice Emping A bowl filled with meat and sauce There are no carrots/tomatoes like that and celery is usually there, so the color is good. When I tasted the soup, wow I was so presumptuous I crowned it the BEST oxtail soup Ive ever eaten (sorry again, if thats too much. But its true, what do you think?  ) Its just that if it has carrots and tomatoes, Im happier because Im a vegetable lover. The meat is just right, not a lot of fat and most importantly the sauce is not too spicy, light but just right. How can it be like that?? The place itself: Its like eating in a very old school era The smell of the room is also like the smell of old wood. If youre bored, the atmosphere at a restaurant or mall is just like that. Try it here okay Wait for my arrival, I will come back to try other menus for sure! (Who am I to ask to wait  )

review_text: The menu has a variety of delicious breads with various choices of flavorings. I usually choose shredded. For something sweet, the classic chocolate sprinkles are quite right on the tongue. Oh yes, dont forget to order black coffee too. From the location, even though it is located between a row of bank shophouses, the atmosphere remains calm and not busy.
The bread is recommended. Gentle.. Keep up the progress, okay?

They sell wheat bread. Wow, wheat bread is really flavored with many variations. It seems like not many people sell wheat bread like this, CMIIW. There are two menus that I bought, namely klepon and choco nougat flavors. Actually, they can buy it individually or in half. The price adjusts accordingly. When it comes to taste, I really like the texture of the bread. Soft and not dry. The taste of the phone is really good, but the nougat is a bit lacking. The portion is quite large, half size can be eaten by two people. Moreover, whole wheat bread keeps you full for longer. The place is quite comfortable and warm. Cool too. The service is friendly. Enough parking for cars and motorbikes. They also sell coffee, you know
review_translated_text: Mereka jual roti gandum. Wow banget roti gandum dikasih flavor dengan banyak varian. Kayaknya belum banyak deh yang jual roti gandum model begini, CMIIW. Menu yg gw beli ada dua, yaitu rasa klepon dan choco nougat. Actually, mereka bisa beli per satuan atau setengah. Harganya menyesuaikan kok. Kalo soal rasa, gw suka banget sama tekstur rotinya. Lembut dan engga kering. Rasa kleponnya berasa banget, tapi yang nougat agak kurang sih. Porsinya cukup besar, ukuran setengah bisa dimakan dua orang. Apalagi roti gandum mengenyangkan lebih lama. Untuk tempatnya cukup nyaman dan warm. Sejuk juga. Pelayanannya ramah. Parkiran cukup untuk mobil dan motor. Mereka juga jual kopi loh

review_text: While looking for a place to have brunch in PIK, I found it through Google and visited on the last day of the year. I wanted to order the BAE Shakshouska and Egg Benedict that I saw in the Google reviews, but the menu had already changed so there were only 3 brunch items (Sancai Bowl, BAE Ceasar Salad, and Bae Toast). Of course, all of the above foods were great, but I was a bit disappointed as I was expecting Egg, Bacon, etc. for breakfast and brunch ^^ The Americano, Hot and Iced, are both at a level that goes well beyond that of a typical coffee shop, and the Drip Coffee tastes good, but the price seems a bit high... The overall store interior and service are very good, so I would visit again if the breakfast menu were improved.

review_text: NIX KTV and Kitchen emerges as a dynamic fusion of entertainment and gastronomy, crafting a unique social experience that stands out in the citys vibrant nightlife scene. This establishment seamlessly blends the exhilarating fun of karaoke with the culinary delight of expertly prepared dishes, making it an ideal spot for food enthusiasts and music lovers alike. The karaoke aspect of NIX KTV and Kitchen offers state-of-the-art equipment, boasting an extensive library of songs that span various genres and languages. Whether youre a seasoned performer or a shy first-timer, the welcoming atmosphere and top-notch sound system ensure every guest feels like a star. The private karaoke rooms are designed with comfort and style in mind, providing a perfect setting for parties, celebrations, or just a night out with friends. On the culinary front, NIX KTV and Kitchen impresses with its diverse menu that features a blend of traditional and innovative dishes. The kitchen takes pride in using high-quality ingredients to create flavorsome meals that satisfy and surprise. From appetizing starters to hearty main courses and delightful desserts, each dish is prepared with care and presented with flair. The menus variety caters to all tastes and dietary preferences, ensuring everyone at the table finds something to relish. review_text: Try Duck Dower at Plaza Atrium Senen. We ordered the menu 1. Spicy Muscovy Muscovy: the portion is jumbo poll, half a baby duck. The sauce has coconut milk but is quite light and has a really delicious spicy taste. Its similar to vegetable lontong soup but this is more savory. The meat is also tender. Unique presentation on the GT fireplace. Price: 50 thousand, including rice 3. Special duck: half a piece of duck, served with 3 variants of chili sauce (shrimp paste, matah and dower). The most delicious is the dower chili sauce. The matah is delicious too and this is the type of chili sauce that is doused in hot oil so there are some that are cooked by the heat of the oil. Another thing is that the chili paste is dominantly sweet and spicy. The duck meat is super tender and juicy, but the flavor of the spices is a bit lacking. review_text: Last year my partner and I ate here very often, in fact we could eat here 3-4 times a month. Because its so delicious and the service is good, surely every time my partner and I get paid, we will agree to eat at Gyuya. but now thats no longer the case, weve moved to eating grill and shabu-shabu at Shabu Hachi. Even though the price is quite expensive, at least the quality of the meat and the service provided is very good. I was disappointed eating at Gyuya starting in January this year and I was really disappointed with Gyuya. Firstly, I asked for Wagyu beef because there wasnt any in the refrigerator, so I asked for the one there, but instead we were given Wagyu beef which was no longer fresh and tasted very bad. The second time we asked for tissue, we talked to the ladies 3 times but we didnt give it, until finally I got annoyed and used the tissue I brought. thirdly, the service is very poor. From there I decided not to eat at Gyuya anymore when I went to the atrium, but yesterday, April 9, I tried to eat at Gyuya again, because that night I wanted to eat grill. but because it was already 7 pm and the position was perfect in the atrium, my partner and I agreed to try eating at Gyuya again with the agreement if the food and servers at Gyuya this time are the same as the last time we went to Gyuya, then my partner and I will definitely have it. I wont eat at Gyuya anymore, I dont even want to recommend it to friends. But what I was afraid of would happen again, I asked my lady for Wagyu meat and it came out that Wagyu meat was no longer fresh, frozen, so I put the meat back in the refrigerator. Then I asked for a tissue and it wasnt delivered, even though I had said/asked him several times. Miss is wearing a white shirt and black pants, looks like shes still training, right? but the problem is that the tissue wasnt delivered, its trivial, but its zero for me. Please improve the quality and also the way the employees serve customers.

review_text: Review for Gyu-Ya AYCE: Pros: - Affordable price: I was pleasantly surprised by the affordable price of the all-you-can-eat (AYCE) menu at Gyu-Ya, especially considering it is located in a Jakarta mall. For just 320k, two people can enjoy a variety of grilled and shabu-shabu dishes. - Wide selection of soup options: Gyu-Ya offers a diverse range of soup options to accompany your meal. I particularly enjoyed the laksa soup, which had a delicious flavor that was not overly sour. Its a great alternative for those who want to try something other than the usual tom yum soup. - Abundance of side dishes: The AYCE menu at Gyu-Ya includes a generous selection of side dishes, such as chicken satay, green mussels with Padang sauce, fried snacks, dim sum, fried rice, and more. There is even a refreshing chocolate ice drink available. - Variety of shabu-shabu choices: Gyu-Ya provides a wide variety of options for shabu-shabu, including seafood like clams and even eggs. The selection is impressive and allows for a customized dining experience. Cons: - Portion control for meat: One minor drawback is that the meat portions are served in containers, which limits the amount you can take at once. However, the taste is still enjoyable. - Inattentive staff: During my visit, I encountered a slight issue with one of the staff members. When I asked where to get the beef, she responded with a vague answer instead of simply directing me to the nearby refrigerator. Overall, Gyu-Ya AYCE offers an affordable and enjoyable dining experience. The menu provides a wide range of options, including delicious soups, abundant side dishes, and a variety of shabu-shabu choices. Just be aware of the portion control for the meat and the possibility of encountering some inattentive staff.

One of the AYCEs in the atrium plaza. There are packages for 129,000 (all) and 99,000 (hotpot only). The price includes drinks and dessert. And just a note, the price does not include 10% service charge and 11% VAT. With an additional 21% the price is quite good. For meat choices, there are chicken and beef with several spices. There are premium meats, namely wagyu and saikoro, but when I went there the wagyu was no longer refilled. There are also several kinds of boiled ones and they are quite varied. There are 4 kinds of drinks, plus fruit ice. If you want fizzy drinks, you can do that too, just tell the waiter and it will be brought to your table.

review_text: The most delicious place to eat in Menteng Square, the cleanest and most comfortable place to work & hang out. Including the toilet is also very clean. My favorite menu is Pocket Grill Cheese Beef & Cheese Beef Original (with Sourdough bread). The drinks are also delicious, especially the Palm Milk & Mocha Coffee. Drink prices start at around 24k and the Pocket Grill is 47k. But for that price its worth it with really delicious food, just the right portions and overall good service. Oh yes, the WiFi is also very reliable. Opening hours are in the afternoon, starting at 2 pm and closing at 9. The decor and ambience of the place are also vintage in line with their cheeses and grill concept. The employees are also friendly here. So this is one of the rare gems in JakPus

Harga minumannya mulai sekitaran 24k dan Pocket Grillnya 47k. Tapi dengan harga segitu sepadan dg makanan yang enak banget, porsi pas dan keseluruhan layanan yang oke. Oiya, WiFinya juga reliable banget. Jam bukanya memang siang, mulai dari 2 siang dan tutup jam 9. Decor dan ambience tempatnya juga vintage setema dengan keju-kejuan dan grill concept mereka. Pegawainya juga ramah di sini. So this is one of rare gems di JakPus

review_text: Sharing a little information regarding Es Teler 77 Atrium Plaza. I came here on July 4 2022 in the morning around 10.40 WIB. 1) Payments are not accepted in cash (okay maybe to prevent the transmission of Covid 19) but when you want to use the D*NA application the cashier says you cant even though it says there is a D*NA Application. 2) Cashier service for ladies, I dont know whose name I dont know because they dont use an ID card or name plate at all JUDES, there is no friendly word. Explaining number 1 briefly again is impossible. 3) For the food I ordered, one of them was Otak Otak. I thought it was still warm, but it turned out to be cold. Whether it was fried earlier or not, I dont know, for the super meatballs the sauce is bland, whether it doesnt have enough salt or something, its basically different from Es Teller 77 in other places. We ask that the relevant management read this article to improve it so that in the future the service will be good and people will like eating here. On Gmaps alone, the reviews are 3.4, for the class of Es Teller 77 which already has a name, it should immediately improve so that it is not displaced by other brands that prioritize Complete Service, Effective Communication and ZERO COMPLAIN.

Menjelaskan perihal nomor 1 juga singkat sekali lagi GK BISA. 3) untuk makanan saya Pesan ada salah satunya Otak Otak saya kira masih hangat dong ternyata dingin. Entah gorengnya dari tadi atau bagaimana saya tidak tahu, untuk Bakso supernya kuah nya hambar entah kurang garam atau gimana pokoknya beda dengan Es Teller 77 ditempat lain. review_text: Oh, I actually only review when Im in the mood, but this time I have to review this place because I really love this place. The atmosphere is really suitable for hanging out alone, or for couples, it can be really romantic, or for those with friends/family, it will definitely be fun to chat here. The place is really beautiful and cool, the views are trees, water, birds, planes, boats and the sky. You cant hear the sound of vehicles from outside, and its really just the sound of nature and relaxing music playing in the cafe, so its really calm. Well, occasionally there are sounds of planes and boats too, hehehe The food and drinks are also delicious. I tried the MH special tea (kiwi mint) and the rice mixed with chicken. The tea is fresh and the mixed rice is also delicious. I really like shredded chicken, yummm. The employees are also friendly, especially the guys at the cashier/barista. When I ordered, I asked if the special tea was sweet or not, then he deliberately made one that wasnt that sweet so it really suited my taste. Indeed, if we want to go to this cafe, we have to pay a ticket to enter the mangrove area. On a normal day I pay 30 thousand + 20 thousand for car parking. For a motorbike its 10 thousand... but its really worth it for me. Fix it, Ill be back sometime!

Tempatnya beneran asri dan adem, pemandangan nya itu pohon, air, burung, pesawat, boat dan langit. Ga kedengeran suara kendaraan dari luar, dan bener2 cuma suara alam sama relaxing music yg diputer di cafenya, jd beneran tenang deh. Yah sesekali ada suara pesawat sama boat juga sih hehehe Untuk makanan dan minuman nya juga enak2. Aku cobain mh special tea (kiwi mint) dan nasi campur ayam nya. Tea nya seger dan nasi campur nya juga enak. Aku suka banget suir2 ayam nya yummm. Pegawai nya juga ramah2, apalagi mas2 yg di kasir/barista nya. Aku pas order tanya mh special tea manis atau enggak, trus mas nya sengaja bikinin yg ga gitu manis jd cocok banget sama selera aku. Emang sih kalau mau ke cafe ini kita harus bayar tiket masuk kawasan mangrove nya. Aku di hari biasa bayar 30rb + 20rb untuk parkir mobil. Kalo motor 10rb.. tp beneran worth it sih kalo buat aku. Vows is located in the middle of a shophouse-like building, its already on the maps so you dont need to worry about getting lost. The place is not too big, with a Japanese-style interior that is simple but nice and attractive. Cleanliness is okay and service is quite good. There are toilets, wifi and sockets near each table so its quite supportive for those who want to drink coffee while using their laptop. The menu here is only limited to drinks and mostly coffee menus, while there are only two non-coffee menus, namely chocolate and matcha. All drinks here are available in 2 cup sizes, namely regular and large. I tried the Okinawa Latte in a large size (32,000), I think the price is quite affordable because the cup size is also high. This Okinawa latte is iced coffee with coconut brown sugar, the milk used is soy milk but you can also replace it with almond milk or oatmeal. In my opinion, the coffee taste is not too strong, the soy milk tastes really good and the sweetness is just right. Honestly, I personally dont really enjoy drinking coffee because its not bitter at all, its delicious and it just tastes healthier because they use soy milk and coconut brown sugar which are plant-based and contain less sugar.
review_translated_text: Vows ini lokasinya ada di tengah-tengah bangunan semacam ruko gitu, udah ada di maps sih jadi nggak perlu khawatir nyasar. Tempatnya gak terlalu besar, dengan interior ala-ala Jepang yang simple tapi bagus dan menarik. Kebersihannya oke dan pelayanan cukup bagus. Ada toilet, wifi dan stop kontak di dekat setiap meja jadi cukup mendukung buat yang mau ngopi sambil laptopan. Menu disini hanya sebatas menu minuman saja dan lebih banyak menu kopi sedangkan menu non kopinya hanya ada dua yaitu chocolate dan matcha. Semua minuman disini tersedia dalam 2 ukuran cup yaitu reguler dan large. Aku coba Okinawa Latte dengan ukuran large (32.000), menurutku harganya cukup affordable sih karena ukuran cupnya juga tinggi. Okinawa latte ini adalah iced coffee dengan coconut brown sugar, susu yang digunakan adalah soy milk tapi bisa juga diganti ke almond milk atau oatly. Menurutku rasa kopinya gak terlalu strong, soy milknya berasa banget dan manisnya tergolong pas. Jujur aku pribadi malah nggak terlalu ngerasa minum kopi karena nggak pahit sama sekali, enak sih dan rasanya lebih sehat aja karena mereka pakai soy milk dan coconut brown sugar yang plant-based dan kandungan gulanya lebih sedikit.

review_text: This is my first time eating at Platinum. Ordered sirloin steak... when it arrived, it turned out it was a hot plate model that had to be cooked first like a pep**er lu*ch. I think it will immediately become holy  . What Im confused about is that there are fries there that are already cooked (the color is already a nice golden brown), along with green beans, carrots and corn that look like theyve been boiled. Then why do you put it on the hot plate too? It will cook and then overcook, aka it will burn hahaha As for the steak, it wasnt tender enough :(. Tbh, I cut the sirloin and it took a lot of effort, to the point where it was dry (maybe because I was pregnant, I got irritated easily). Yes, you can imagine how rich the steak would be because just cutting it made it dry like that hahaha. As for the sauce, I think its a little salty. Then for drinks, I just ordered mango smoothies because it reduces caffeine for pregnant women. And it turns out its really muaniiss, I dont know if its sweet from the mango, or the sugar, or... from the sweetened condensed milk (?) But I dont think its from the mango, as sweet as the mango is, it doesnt seem like that much. But its delicious, but its really sweet, please.
review_translated_text: Ini first time makan di platinum. Pesen sirloin steak... pas dateng, ternyata modelnya hot plate yg harus dimasak dulu kaya pep**er lu*ch gitu. Kirain yg langsung jadi kaya holy . Yg saya bingung, disitu kan ada kentang goreng yg emang base nya udah mateng (warna nya udah cakep golden brown gitu), sama buncis, wortel, jagung yg keliatannya udah direbus gitu. Terus kenapa ditaro juga di hot plate nya yak, kan jadinya ikut kemasak terus jadi overcook alias gosong wkwk Untuk steak nya kurang empuk :(. Tbh, saya motong sirloin nya perlu effort banget, sampe keringetan (mungkin karna lagi hamil juga sih jadi gampang gerah). Ya bisa dibayangin lah ya steak nya kaya gimana karna motong nya aja sampe keringetan gitu wkwk. Untuk sauce nya, menurut saya keasinan dikit. Terus untuk minumannya, saya pesen mango smoothies aja karna ngurangin kafein buat bumil. Dan ternyata muaniiss bangeett wkwk gak tau itu manis dari mangga nya kah, atau gula nya kah, atau... dari susu kental manis (?) Tapi kayanya kalo dari mangga nya nggak deh, se manis2 nya mangga kayanya gak sampe segitunya. Tapi enak sih, tapi kemanisan banget plis.

review_text: Location on the 2nd floor of Plaza Atrium Senen Near the elevator, near Miniso

Platinum in the atrium plaza is located on the 2nd floor.. Visited here during fasting last Tuesday. So at Platinum we dont accept bookings during fast breaking time. Only those whose personnel are complete can be let in. As a result, even though we were B5 and there were 3 new arrivals, we were brave enough to say that everything was complete. We were led to a table with 4 chairs. But it turned out that the 1 empty chair was immediately taken back by the lady. The lady said that next time someone comes, they wont promise a seat because thats the system. But luckily when our 2 friends came later, the waiters there still didnt bother looking for extra chairs After being a bit confused about what menu to choose, I finally decided to order the Hainanese spicy and sour chicken because I saw that it had tofu and it looked fresh from the picture. When you taste it, its not bad. The Hainanese rice is delicious, the tofu is delicious, the chicken is crunchy but the sauce is more dominant in sourness, it doesnt feel spicy at all. The only vegetable there is a leaf of mustard greens in the broth.. Theres nothing special about the Spiderman menu, except the usual sausages and French fries that are sold packaged in supermarkets.
review_translated_text: Platinum di atrium plaza ini terletak d lantai 2.. Berkunjung kemari saat bukber hri selasa lalu. Jaadi di platinum ini ga terima bookingan tampat selama waktu buka puasa. Siapa yg personilnya udah lengkap baru bisa dikasih masuk. Alhasil walaupun kami b5 dan yang baru datang 3 kami nekat aja bilang udah lengkap semua. Diantarkanlah kaami ke meja dengan 4 kursi. Tapi ternyata 1 kursi yg kosong itu langsung di ambil lagi sm mbaknya. Mbaknya bilang kl nanti ada yg datang lagi, mereka gbs janjiin kursi krn memang sistemnya begitu. Tp untungnya saat 2 teman kami datang belakangan, pelayan2 disana masih mau direpotkan untuk mencarikan kursi tambahan Setelah agak bingung mau pilih menu apa akhirnya memutuskan pesan ayam asam pedas hainan karena lihat ada tofunya dan kelihatan segar aja dari gambarnya. Saaat dicicip, lumayan lah ya. Nasi hainannya enak, tofunya enak, ayamnya crunchy tp untuk saucenya lebih dominan ke asamnya, pedasnya tidak terasa sama sekali. Sayurnya cuma terdapat selembar sawi di dalam kuah kaldu.. Kalau menu spiderman sih ga ada istimewanya cm sosis dan french fries biasa yg dijual kemasan di supermarket2 gitu.

review_text: One interesting culinary experience in Central Jakarta is enjoying Coto Makassar which is open 24 hours. I happened to arrive around 19:00, that night the weather was cloudy all day, so it was really nice to eat warm food. Coto Makassar has been around for a long time since the 1970s and has become a favorite of many customers. Here there are 2 choices of filling, meat or mixed, for those who like offal like me, of course you wont miss this delicious and savory dish with gravy, especially if you add spicy chili sauce and fresh orange. We can eat Coto with buras or ketupas which are provided on the table. Although the taste of Coto Makassar here is tasty, it is made a little bland, we can adjust it ourselves because they prepare salt, soy sauce and other spices at the table. Apart from spices, buras and ketupat, salted eggs and pastels are also served on the table as additional side dishes. The meat filling is quite abundant, especially when eaten with ketupat and other side dishes, it is filling. Eating Coto here is highly recommended. There are also lots of parking spaces and dining tables. Come on, for those of you who have just come home from work and are hungry after a long day of work, Coto Makassar Senen can be comfort food to restore your enthusiasm.
review_translated_text: Satu pengalaman kuliner menarik di Jakarta Pusat adalah menikmati Coto Makassar yang buka 24 jam. Kebetulan saya datang sekitar jam 19:00, malam itu cuaca memang mendung seharian, sehingga nikmat sekali menyantap makanan yang hangat-hangat. Coto Makassar ini telah lama berdiri sejak 1970-an dan telah menjadi favorit banyak pelanggan. Disini ada 2 pilihan isi, daging atau campur, bagi yang suka jeroan seperti saya tentu tidak akan melewatkan santapan lezat dan gurih berkuah apa lagi ditambahkan sambal pedas dan jeruk segar. Kita bisa menyantap Coto dengan buras ataupun ketupas yang telah disediakan diatas meja. Rasa Coto Makassar disini meskipun gurih tetapi memang dibuat sedikit hambar, kita bisa menyesuaikan sendiri karena mereka menyiapkan garam, kecap, dan bumbu2 lain di meja. Selain dari bumbu, buras dan ketupat, di meja juga disajikan telur asin dan pastel sebagai tambahan lauk. Isian dagingnya cukup melimpah apa lagi dimakan dengan ketupat dan lauk lainnya jadi mengenyangkan. Makan Coto disini cukup rekomended. Tempat parkir dan meja makannya juga banyak. Yuklah buat kalian yang baru pulang kantor dan lapar setelah seharian kerja, Coto Makassar Senen ini bisa menjadi comfort food untuk mengembalikan semangat.

review_text: Looking for breakfast near the inn. Coto appears. Hmmm. Its time for breakfast with Coto. But then read the good reviews. Finally I decided to go there. The first bite, how come its not salty... its true what another reviewer said, we have to mix it ourselves. I put in salt, lemon, chili sauce, soy sauce. I swear this coto is really delicious!!!!!!! Coto Makassar Senen Syamsul Daeng Ngawing
review_text: As a first-time diner, I arrived at the establishment on a Friday at approximately 12:00 PM. Upon arrival, I noticed a substantial crowd.   I placed an order for Coto Makassar, specifically requesting beef and offal (tripe and lungs).     Regrettably, I neglected to request the inclusion of raw egg yolk, which I intend to rectify during my next visit.   The dish was presented in a diminutive bowl, yet it proved to be deceptively substantial.   I highly recommend pairing it with Buras (Buginese Rice Cakes) to enhance the culinary experience.   I also sampled their Shrimp Bakwan, but I must admit that it fell short of my expectations, exuding an unpleasant odor.    In terms of accessibility, I advise utilizing public transportation, as parking options are scarce in the vicinity.    #Foodie #LocalEats #IndonesianCuisine Parking: Better using public transport.

review_text: Haidilao Hot Pot @Pik Avenue The place is really unique. The restaurant is located at Pik Avenue Mall, fourth floor. Menu has a lot of tasty food. The Hot Pot is known for its popularity because of theres many kinds of options for the soup. Theres many kinds of sauce and youll be able to mix it. Theres also lots of drinks options. These are including: Soft Drinks Lemon Tea Water Some of these drinks can be freely refill as much as you want. Its free. Desserts/Snacks also has many kind of options. Ice cream flavour is different everyday. The restaurant is indoor. Theres a lot of seats near windows. Native Chinese people usually visit this place. Chef is really hardworker, they prepare almost everything. Waiters also are hardworkers, they will immediately refill your drinks on sight. Everytime you visit the place, you can obtain a screen wiper for free. Theres a playground for kids. Walls are brown-ish oak woods. Lots of decoration, well decorated. For the menu, you are provided an ipad to order. You need to add your G-Mail for your first time visiting this place. Youre also giving a chance to spin a wheel to receive prize for your first time visit. Fruits are delivered at the end for desserts. Atmosphere are BUSY, its really crowded. Dont go there at the weekend. Great views from the windows. Theres a VIP room, its really expensive. Well-Crafted-Made Restaurant. 5 Stars. Vegetarian options: Vegetarian Options. The Hot Pot, Soup are recommend for Vegetarian. Eggs are also here. Ice cream is delicious. Super corn is also delicious. Kid-friendliness: Kid-friendliness. This restaurant is Kid-Friendliness. Staffs are friendly towards Kids/Minor/Fetus. Theres a playground for kids. Mostly kids after eating goes to playground so they can have fun and enjoy their time. Theres also TV for kids/childrens. Mostly plays Cocomelon. Childrens are given goodie bag. Wheelchair accessibility: Wheelchair accessibility. No Wheelchair Accessibility.

The balado eggplant is quite delicious. The restaurant is spacious, the parking area is also spacious. Downstairs there is a mini market then go up to the 2nd floor to the room and dining table.

I come to this place at 10AM-ish on weekdays to do some work. Here s what I think. Ambience: 4.5/5 The place is divided into 2 area, the first one is located under escalator, and the second one is connected to outdoor space. I like the way they divide the seating. The inner side (the one under escalator) has less tables, and the space between each tables are pretty wide. I suppose the concept for this area is like a coffee shop, similar to starbucks . This zone is suitable for those people who want some kind of privacy (work, reading, focus, etc.). They also have freshly made pastries showcased in this area and they smell so nice! However, the lighting here is quite poor. Although it gives you a cozy and homey feel, people don t usually come to this area as their first choice. Only when the other side is full, then the customers look for some space here. The second area has better lighting since it s connected to outdoor. They also put some green decoration to make the place look fresh and inviting. Seatings are pretty close between each tables and you can combine 1-2 tables if you re coming to dine with some friends. The concept of this area is much like a restaurant cafe, suitable for informal meetings, casual hang out, etc. I would say this area represents the name of the restaurant: Social Affair, where you can socialize as long as you wish while enjoying some food and beverage. The only downside of this zone, is that since each tables are pretty close to each other, you can somehow hear the conversation of the other parties. It s ok when others  conversation is something light and insignificant, but can be quite annoying (or maybe exciting to some?) when they started gossiping  yes, most customers here are a group of ladies. Food: 3/5 I ordered their Baked Eggs, accompanied by classic flavored tea (hibiscus). The portion is just nice for me since I came for brunch. This dish has 3-4 meatballs, baked with 2 eggs and tomato based sauce on a small cast iron. There are 2 slices of sourdough bread to dip with the tomato sauce too. Much like a shakshouka. The meatballs are a little too rough and dry. You may want to chew it a few additional times, or otherwise it will feel too coarse for your throat. The positive thing though, it means the meatballs are pure meat with less fat and no additional flour to tenderize it. Perfect for those on diet But, The tomato sauce tasted VERY strong and quite overwhelming if you eat it just like that. The sourness is overwhelming to a point that it feels like you re eating tomato puree directly just like that. Thankfully, the dish comes with sourdough to neutralize it. (Although, the quantity is not enough to finish the whole dish). I don t hate the Baked Eggs, but this dish has made me desperately need a light drinks to neutralize the overwhelming tomato sauce. Thus, I ordered the flavored classic tea: blackcurrant & hibiscus tea. If I have to compare, I still prefer Livingstone s shakshouka compared to this one. But, of course, different price tags produce different quality.; Service:4/5 Since they divided the place to 2 areas, sometimes it s pretty hard to get the waiters  attention, especially when you re sitting near the outdoor zone. Either you have to raise your voice so the waiters (and the other customers) hear you, or wait until one of them is heading to your direction and wave. Regardless, I only need to be patient for 5-6 min, before I caught one of the waiters  attention. Not bad  unless you re in a hurry. Overall, I think I should give this cafe another try. Perhaps next time I ll try their famous croffle and pastries. Additional note: They do not accept cash payments. Only cards and QRIS payments are accepted.

Theres pulut srikaya, theres lupis, theres vegetable rice cake which is quite delicious. milk and tea made into one glass.. Unique isnt it... haha.. You have to try the Rich Toast Package, the bread is delicious, the 1/2 cooked egg is very fresh so it doesnt smell bad, recommended, its all delicious..! Standard price $$$ Parking can be in the side shop so there is no need to queue in the building yard which is not too large.

review_text: A must visit eatery place. JX Kopitien is one of the busiest kopitiam similar with kopitiam in Singapore and Penang. It provides delicious traditional food and a friendly service to its customers. Start your day with a hot milk coffee and half boiled eggs with Kaya Toast. You dont want to miss the kweitiau goreng, mie tomat, Porridge, mie Acim, nasi campur and lontong to name a few of your choice Leave some room for their autentic dessert such as Lupis, klepon, bubur ketan itam, ongol ongol to complete your appetite. I would surely recommend you to try all their favorite food while you are there in your hometown

review_text: Ahh...Jia Xiang Kopitien... A must go to eatery so fond to my heart whenever I have a chance to go back to Jakarta and visit my family. This place literally oozed warmth and enveloped you in a great ambiance, positive energy and awesome food!! It was hard to not overeat at JX.  The foods were cooked to perfection, the drinks tasted fresh and not scalding hot nor just lukewarm.  You can tell this place is tightly run and the people that work there care and want to be there!  We ordered Char kwetiaw, Mie Acim (despite the name this noodle is the bomb!), Mie keriting, Lu Rou Fan, Kaya Toast, Lupis, Ongol2, Pulut Srikaya and Pisang Goreng.  Every ONE of them is good! E V E R Y....O N E!!!! They were out of their Nasi Sayur and Lontong Sayur so these are the two items I would hit up on my future visit! Give this place a try and see for yourself.  If you like it, great!! The place is always packed but it never turn people away and deter them from coming back. I sure am looking forward to go back to my Jia Xiang in the near future and eat at JX Kopitien!

review_text: Located in a small alley, Jl Melati No 12 Senen, Kramat, Central Jakarta. This restaurant is a legend, among the Chinese. Among of its signature dishes are: Fried Frog Legs, Lomie, and Mun Kiao ( sauteed fried dumpling with vegetables). So we ordered them all. Fried Frog Legs  (IDR 110.000) Mun Kiao (IDR 85.000) Lomie (IDR 85.000) Cucumber Pickle (IDR 10,000) Mun Kiau is the signature dish of Pan Am, which might be rare to find in other places. The fried dumplings are sauteed with veggies (white mustard, mushroom, and cauliflower). The dumplings, of course are not too crispy, as it is dipped into the thick soup. The veggies feel fresh. All these combinations will surely make your tongue dance. Lomie is served with veggies, prawns, fish meatballs. The noodles is cooked Al dente. Blended perfectly with tasty thick soup. Fried Frog Legs cooked with butter. Crispy and tasty. Cucumber pickles is tasty. It is listed in the menu, so you need to order it. In general, all menu is tasty. Its my second visit and I fall for Mun Kiau. The dishes are tyypical of Chinese Peranakan dishes. During my first visit, I ordered Beed Bistik, which is also tasty. Verdict : 5.0 / 5.0 Price : Its a bit pricey, but the portion is pretty big, can be for 2 people. The only downside is the location, which located in a narrow alley. However, it is still passable and cars can be parked in front of this restaurant.

This traditional Chinese food restaurant is a hidden gem in Jakartas Senen neighborhood. This long-established Chinese eatery offers a delightful experience for those seeking authentic flavors in a simple setting.

Chinese food that looks quiet but turns out the food is delicious. You really have to try the Lomie, its even tastier with the chili sauce. Fu yung hai is a typical dense filling. Other dishes are also delicious, rock frogs are delicious. Overall everything is delicious..
review_translated_text: Chinese food yg keliatannya sepi tapi ternyata makanannya enak. Harus banget coba Lomienya tambah enak pake sambelnya.  Fu yung hai tipikal yg padat isian. Masakan lainnya juga enak kodok batu enak. Overall enak semua..

review_text: The beefsteak is really delicious!! Typical of Jadoel Chinese food, which uses English sauce, only this sauce tends to be a bit salty, and the beef is first chopped, made into sticks, then cut into small pieces. not the type that is fried in flour first You have to ask for additional fries, because they are really delicious!! If you order pork steak, the meat is fried in flour first, but the seasoning is the same as beef steak The Mun Kiaw Mien dumplings are also the best!! The thinnest and juiciest dumpling skin Ive ever eaten. You have to order too The place is a bit in a narrow alley, at most you can only park 2 cars Her aunt is very friendly, Even though the place is small, it turns out its really legendary!
review_translated_text: Bistik Sapi nya enak banget sih!! Tipikal masakan Chinese Food jadoel, yang pake saus inggris, cuma ini sausnya agak condong asin, dan sapi nya itu  dicincang dulu, dijadiin stik ,lalu dipotong kecil-kecil. bukan tipe yang digoreng tepung dulu Wajib minta additional kentang goreng, karena enak banget!! Kalo pesen Bistik Babi, dagingnya digoreng tepung dulu, tapi bumbunya sama kayak bistik sapi Pangsit Mun Kiaw Mien nya juga juarak sih!! Kulit pangsit tertipis dan tergarig yg pernah gw makan. Wajib pesen juga nih Tempatnya agak masuk gang sempit paling cuma bisa parkir 2 mobil lah Tante nya ramah banget, Walau tempatnya kecil, tapi ternyata ini legend banget loh!

review_text: It was the right choice for me personally, who at that time was rainy and hungry. This restaurant serves authentic halal ramen and is famous for its chicken ramen. This restaurant also offers lunch packages that include gyoza. The menu prices at Sugakiya Ramen are relative, starting from IDR 30,000 to IDR 40,000 per person but its worth it with the filling portions. This restaurant also offers a comfortable and friendly atmosphere, as well as good and friendly service. Especially Sugakiya at this station... try eating ramen sitting next to the glass like this once in a while.
review_translated_text: Menjadi pilihan tepat untuk saya pribadi yang kala itu kehujanan dan lapar. Restoran ini menyajikan ramen halal yang otentik dan terkenal dengan chicken ramennya. Restoran ini juga menawarkan paket makan siang yang sudah termasuk gyoza. Harga menu di Sugakiya Ramen relatif ya, mulai dari Rp30.000 hingga Rp40.000 per orang namun worth it dengan porsi yang mengenyangkan. Restoran ini juga menawarkan suasana yang nyaman dan ramah, serta pelayanan yang baik dan ramah. Terlebih Sugakiya yang ada di stasiun ini  coba sesekali makan ramen duduk dekat kaca begini.

review_text: One alternative when you want to find a delicious & comfortable place to eat at Senen Station. I came around 7pm, I wanted to try curry rice, unfortunately the rice wasnt ready yet. Finally tried Mazesoba ORI and special ramen. Both are delicious, the ramen soup is also delicious. Eggs can be cooked or  1/2 cooked. Oh yes Ocha free refill. Standard price. The place is clean, the service is friendly and the food is served quite quickly. Its just that we were a bit annoyed by the staff who, when not serving customers, joked around by talking & laughing quite loudly. FYI, there is a special place to put large suitcases/bags there.
review_translated_text: Salah satu alternatif ketika ingin cari tempat makan yang enak & nyaman di stasiun Senen. Saya datang sekitar habis jam 7 malam, mau cobain curry rice, sayangnya nasi belum ready. Akhirnya nyobain Mazesoba ORI dan special ramen. Keduanya enak, kuah ramennya juga gurih. Telur bisa rikues matang atau  1/2 matang ya. Oh ya Ocha free refill. Harga standar. Tempatnya bersih, pelayanan ramah dan penyajian makanan cukup cepat. Hanya saja kami agak terganggu dengan para staff yang pada saat tidak melayani pelanggan, mereka bercanda dengan berbicara & ketawa cukup keras. FYI, ada tempat khusus taruh koper/ tas besar ya disana.

review_text: Compared to the taste, too expensive

This is the first time I entered a cafe and sat for a moment and was immediately scolded by the staff. So I really want to have lunch, but I have an urgent meeting. Ive already given the code to the waiter when I want to order, the customer also knows himself, whats the point of having a meeting at Olatte because theres no public wifi (I use a cellphone hotspot), but the waiter repeatedly comes in with a loud voice and pretends to want to take a table because there are other customers (who dont exist). Its crazy, he came to my table and spoke to me while half shouting and repeatedly, deliberately disrupting my meeting. Then pass by pushing the food table loudly. There is no respect for customers and I really dont feel wrong, Im afraid just because the customer hasnt ordered (I sat for 5 minutes and they were already angry). After the meeting I complained about the way they treated customers and they didnt care and there was no apology. I, who was going to have lunch there, finally gave up and went home. I submitted my complaint to RSCM in writing regarding the restaurants treatment of patients. Hopefully my feedback will be heard and made improvements.

Gilak sih, datang ke meja saya dan ngomong ke saya sambil setengah teriak dan berkali2, sengaja mengganggu meeting sy. Lalu lewat dgn mendorong meja makanan kenceng2. Ga ada respect ke customer dan bener2 tdk merasa salah, ketakutan hanya krn customer blm memesan (sy br duduk 5 menit mereka sdh marah). Sehabis meeting sy komplen dgn cara mereka memperlakukan customer dan mereka tdk peduli dan tdk ada permintaan maaf. Sy yg tadinya mau lunch di sana akhirnya ilfil dan pulang. Sy masukkan komplen sy ke pihak RSCM secara tertulis dgn perlakuan pihak resto kepada pasien. Semoga feedback sy didengar dan dijadikan perbaikan.

review_text: Top

Ice Cappuccino, the ice is in a blender, no milk at all.. The seller is not friendly at all, there is no explanation, even though I have asked.. Over price.. The drink was ready, I paid for it, I immediately told him to throw it in the trash...

The most delicious Olatte Fried Rice in RSCM Kencana and Pusat Every time you come, its always busy... its never quiet... especially at lunch time... but you always get a table... hehe Several times outpatient and inpatient for 3 weeks... Always order Olatte fried rice to eat there. The rice is fried when ordered so its still hot and delicious... the price is hospital standard and the taste is very attractive... so its worth it... The fried rice includes fried egg, crispy chicken fillet, sprinkled with anchovies... plus crackers. At first I thought it was just normal, but when I tried it I was addicted... really recommended... The chicken is tender, the meat is really good. The taste of the spices is also really good, the chicken skin is crispy and crunchy... Im hungry again when I write the review... Recommend it to my wife, but she also wants to buy it again... and she also said the Olatte fried rice is delicious... recommended! Have you ever tried other noodle menus, its also delicious to eat in the room... Even though its busy, there are lots of people waiting to be served quickly. So be patient and wait... Operational hours close around 6pm, so for those who want to have dinner, order at 5pm for a meal in the inpatient room, suitable for waiting for patients because the food is delicious and gives you a mood booster... Suggestion: If you can close at 7 pm it will be even better for those waiting for patients to order dinner. Especially if there is a delivery service to Kencana inpatient care. Its sure to sell... Keep up the good work Olatte

review_text: Olatte is located in the RSCM golden building. The template is quite comfortable, unfortunately there is no wifi available. The food is quite varied, ranging from pastry, pasta to oxtail soup. I tried ice chocolate mint (51k) and pasta carbonara (58k). In my opinion, the ice chocolate is superduper mega overpriced because its really B, the size is very standard and the taste is the same, and there are no toppings. The pasta price is still reasonable because the portion is not too small, the meat cuts are adequate but the taste is a bit too salty. I understand that because in a hospital the prices go up, for food it is still reasonable but in my opinion drinks are a bit excessive. Oh yes, here you can order salad wrapped, in a bowl or as a croissant filling, its quite interesting to try.
review_translated_text: Olatte ini letaknya di gedung kencana RSCM. Temlat nya cukup nyaman sayang belum tersedia wifi. Makananya cukup beragam, mulai dari pastry, pasta hingga sop buntut. Saya cobain ice chocolate mint (51k) dan pasta carbonara (58k). Ice chocolate nya menurut saya superduper mega overpriced sih soalnya B banget, ukuran sangat standar dan begitupula rasanya, serta tidak ada topping. Pasta nya harganya masih masuk akal karena porsi nya tidak terlalu sedikit, potongan daging nya adekuat namun rasanya agak terlalu asin. Saya mengerti karena di RS maka harganya jadi melonjak, untuk makanan masih masuk akal namun menurut saya minuman agak berlebihan. Oiya disini bisa pesan salad yang di wrap, bowl ataupun sebagai isian croissant, cukup menarik sih untuk dicoba.

review_text: Food Street Kramat is a place to eat that offers a variety of delicious Padang cuisine. Located in Central Jakarta, this place offers a lively atmosphere with many visitors coming to enjoy the dishes served. One of the menus that you must try is rendang rice, which tastes very unique with the spices served. Apart from that, there are also Padang satay, chicken curry and balado beef jerky which are no less delicious. Friendly service and affordable prices make Food Street Kramat the right choice for those who want to taste typical Padang dishes in the middle of Jakarta.
review_translated_text: Food Street Kramat merupakan sebuah tempat makan yang menawarkan aneka masakan Padang yang lezat. Berlokasi di Jakarta Pusat, tempat ini menawarkan suasana yang ramai dengan banyaknya pengunjung yang datang untuk menikmati hidangan yang disajikan. Salah satu menu yang wajib dicoba adalah nasi rendang, yang rasanya begitu khas dengan rempah-rempah yang disajikan. Selain itu, ada juga sate padang, gulai ayam, dan dendeng balado yang tak kalah enak. Pelayanan yang ramah dan harga yang terjangkau membuat Food Street Kramat menjadi pilihan yang tepat bagi mereka yang ingin mencicipi hidangan khas Padang di tengah kota Jakarta.

The location is remote, hidden, near the Muara Baru fish market, there are no signs, even in front of the building you cant see the name of this cake shop. So they are on the 2nd floor, located in the same building as Sushi Masa. The design is attractive, there are enough tables and chairs for eating on site. They sell various cakes that look very attractive, and ice cream with various Japanese flavors such as matcha, sake, hojicha, tofu, yuzu, black sesame, etc. Because we were quite full after eating at Sushi Masa, we only tried a few cakes, such as Mont Blanc (chestnut paste and fresh cream on almond tart), Tora (or opera cake) and Zoe (dark chocolate, caramel and rocher). We love the taste of Tora and Zoe. The service was friendly and fast, but because at that time there was only 1 person, and there were several groups of visitors, so you had to wait.
review_translated_text: Lokasinya terpencil, tersembunyi, dekat pasar ikan Muara Baru, tidak ada petunjuk satu pun, bahkan di depan gedungnya tidak terlihat nama toko kue ini. Jadi mereka berada di lt.2, terletak di dalam gedung yg sama dengan Sushi Masa. Desainnya menarik, ada cukup banyak meja kursi untuk makan di tempat. Mereka menjual berbagai kue yang tampilannya sangat menarik, dan ice cream dengan beragam cita rasa Jepang seperti matcha, sake, hojicha, tofu, yuzu, black sesame, dll. Karena sudah cukup kenyang setelah makan di Sushi Masa, kami hanya mencoba beberapa kuenya, seperti Mont Blanc (chestnut paste dan fresh cream di atas almond tart), Tora (atau opera cake) dan Zoe (dark chocolate, caramel dan rocher). Kami suka dengan rasa Tora dan Zoe. Pelayanannya ramah dan cepat, tapi karena saat itu hanya ada 1 orang, dan pengunjungnya ada beberapa grup, jadi harus menunggu.

I will come back here again.

review_text: Dishes: Service: Cleanliness: Atmosphere: Price: The location is right above Sushi Masa, the parking area is large enough for cars. The dishes are generally deserts, there are various kinds of ice cream and soft ice cream too. Because they say the ice cream comes straight from Japan, the stock tends to run out. What is unique about this ice cream shop is the choice of flavors such as beancurd and seaweed. The soft ice cream is also delicious, very soft. This place has a quiet atmosphere, maybe because the location is quite far, its not worth it just to visit this place.

Hidangannya umumnya desert, ada macam-macam es krim dan soft ice cream juga. Karena katanya es krimnya dari jepang langsung, stoknya suka abis. Yang unik dari warung es krim ini ada di pilihan rasanya seperti kembang tahu dan rumput laut. Soft ice creamnya juga enak, lembut banget. Tempat ini suasanya sepi mungkin karena lokasinya yang cukup jauh, kurang worth it kalau cuman mengunjungi tempat ini.

review_text: small but cozy coffee shop around Muara Karang with a limited number of seats. the parking lot can be quite challenging, especially for cars. when we went there last Sunday, they have guest beans from Blue Bottle Coffee, perfect for espresso-based, and theres a promo of 50% off for 2nd order with the same beans too. if you are a fan of manual brew (V60), fret not, they also have selections of arabica beans. the one that we tried was from Peru (forgot the name), and it was great! clean and well-balanced! the owner is so kind and generous too, he even gave us a free manual brew as a complimentary since we were wondering about the taste of Blue Bottle beans as a filtered coffee. tried their danbing (Taiwanese egg pancake) too and it was good with a generous amount of fillings. the only downside when we were there was the aircon seems not cool enough for us, but, it might be because the temperature of Jakarta was too high recently. definitely will be back again for the coffee when were nearby!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for taking the time to send us such detailed and valuable feedback. Were so glad  you enjoyed our V60   and food!! review_text: Stopping by Magnet Coffee was actually something that wasnt planned, it just happened that I had business around here and was confused about what to have for lunch, finally I remembered that a friend had uploaded about Magnet Coffee on Instagram and also remembered that he said the chicken noodles here were delicious. So I immediately came here with the intention of having coffee and having lunch with chicken noodles. When we arrived at the location, it turned out that the place was empty of visitors, only my brother and I came that afternoon. Its quite a relief because it means you can take photos freely. Magnet Coffee can be said to be small, there is also more seating outside because in the indoor section there is only 1 table and a sofa. They have a 2nd floor which is a semi-rooftop. Its nice to sit on the 2nd floor in the afternoon or evening because during the day it feels like sunbathing :) The cleanliness was just ordinary because when I went upstairs it turned out there was still a table full of dirty glasses. Its a bit understandable because there is only 1 staff who handles everything, I was confused because the staff are not young people but rather gentlemen. At first I underestimated the father, but in fact the father was cool, he made all my orders, both food and drinks, himself. Here I ordered Fried Kwetiauw (17,000), Fried Vermicelli (17,000), Palm Milk Coffee (23,000) and Strawberry Juice (15,000). For kwetiau and vermicelli there are regular, special and seafood choices. The difference between regular and special is only in the number of eggs, so the special has additional fried eggs. With the price under 20K, I think the portion is quite large and the taste is DELICIOUS! Its not bland, the vermicelli and kwetiau are also soft, there are meatball fillings, chicken meat and scrambled eggs, I really like it. The drink is also okay, the milk coffee is creamy but not too sweet, it still balances with the coffee. Strawberry juice is also delicious because it is very fresh, the sourness is still felt but there is sweetness in the milk too.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for visiting and reviewing magnetcoffee   sorry for the inconvenience you, next time you stop by again we will make sure it will be cleaner and free durian spring rolls or suren coffee for you   thank you agoesbanyu magnetcoffee
review_translated_text: Mampir ke Magnet Coffee ini sebenarnya sesuatu yang diluar rencana, cuma kebetulan lagi ada urusan di sekitar sini dan bingung mau makan siang apa, akhirnya inget kalau sempat ada teman yang upload soal Magnet Coffee di Instagram dan ingat juga kalau katanya mie ayam disini enak. Jadi langsung deh meluncur kesini dengan niatan ngopi sekaligus makan siang pakai mie ayam. Begitu sampai lokasi ternyata tempatnya lagi sepi pengunjung, cuma aku dan kakakku aja yang datang di siang itu. Cukup lega rasanya karena berarti bisa foto dengan leluasa. Magnet Coffee ini bisa dibilang mungil, tempat duduknya juga lebih banyak di luar karena di bagian indoor hanya ada 1 meja dan sofa. Mereka punya lantai 2 yang jadi semi rooftop. Enaknya sih duduk di lantai 2 ini di sore atau malam hari karena kalau siang hari rasanya kayak berjemur :) Kebersihannya biasa aja karena pas aku naik ke atas ternyata masih ada meja yang penuh gelas kotor. Agak maklum sih karena cuma ada 1 staff yang handle semuanya, aku aja sampai bingung karena staffnya pun bukan anak muda melainkan agak bapak-bapak. Awalnya sempat underestimate sama si bapak tapi nyatanya si bapak ini keren loh, semua pesananku dia buat sendiri baik makanan dan minuman. Disini aku pesan Kwetiauw Goreng (17.000), Bihun Goreng (17.000), Kopi Susu Aren (23.000) dan Jus Strawberry (15.000). Untuk kwetiau dan bihunnya ada pilihan biasa, spesial dan seafood. Beda antara biasa dan spesial cuma di jumlah telurnya, jadi kalau yang spesial itu ada tambahan telur ceploknya. Dengan harga di bawah 20K menurutku sih porsinya lumayan banyak dan rasanya ENAK! Nggak hambar, bihun dan kwetiaunya juga lembut, ada isian bakso, daging ayam dan telur orak-arik, aku sih suka. Minumannya juga oke, kopi susunya creamy tapi gak terlalu manis, masih balance dengan kopinya. Jus strawberry juga enak karena seger banget, asemnya masih terasa tapi ada manis susunya juga.

The vanilla latte is also delicious. not too sweet. the place is not very big but it is comfortable, lots of places to sit. If asked, would you come back here again? Thats for sure, want to try other menus. the price is really cheap, affordable

Congratulations to Stephen and Ivana for Teras Soka!

review_text: landed in Jakarta and I wanted a coffee, the nearest cafe was this one. I went in, it was a very cozy and nice cafe. at the Bar there was the owner who greeted us with a smile on his face. we chose our coffee, we were surprised that it was extremely good. among other things, I asked the barista what we could do/visit in Jakarta. He was very helpful and kind and explained to us what to do and how. Afterwards, he gave us a note on which he wrote the attractions and his phone number in case we get lost or needed help. I sent him a message to thank him profusely for his help and he offered to serve as a guide and go together to the places we havent reached. And we accepted. Aaron, he gave us an extraordinary experience, for him, an everyday walk, for us a unique experience! He gave us a little tour, explained, showed us around Jakarta, we ate, we felt great! I regret that our experience in Jakarta was so short. Aaron is an extraordinary guy, passionate about coffee. I warmly recommend his coffee and pastry shop. this cafe should definitely be included in the attractions of Jakarta. His coffee is exceptional, was hands down the best one we had in Indonesia. I warmly recommend you to come here for coffee, pastries, atmosphere and for the warm smiles with which you are greeted.
